   #text= """
   #"{{pp-move-indef}}\n{{unreliable sources|date=June 2015}}\n\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2012}}\n{{pp-semi-blp|small=yes}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name            = Jessica Alba\n| image           = Jessica Alba SDCC 2014.jpg\n| caption         = Alba at the 2014 [[San Diego Comic-Con International]]\n| birth_name      = Jessica Marie Alba\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1981|4|28}}\n| birth_place     = {{nowrap|[[Pomona, California]], U.S.}}\n| residence       = {{nowrap|[[Beverly Hills, California]], U.S.}}\n| occupation      = Actress, model, businesswoman\n| years_active    = 1994\u2013present\n| net_worth       = {{gain}} $340 million (May 2016)<ref>http://www.forbes.com/profile/jessica-alba/</ref>\n| spouse          = {{marriage|Cash Warren|2008|}}\n| children        = 2\n}}\n\n'''Jessica Marie Alba''' (born April 28, 1981)<ref name=filmref>{{cite web |url=http://www.filmreference.com/film/6/Jessica-Alba.html/|title=Jessica Alba Biography (1981-) |accessdate=January 28, 2016 |publisher=FilmReference.com| archivedate= October 17, 2015| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20151017080224/http://www.filmreference.com/film/6/Jessica-Alba.html | deadurl=no}}</ref> is an American actress, model and businesswoman.<ref>{{Cite web|title = How Jessica Alba Built A $1 Billion Company, And $200 Million Fortune, Selling Parents Peace Of Mind|url = http://www.forbes.com/sites/clareoconnor/2015/05/27/how-jessica-alba-built-a-1-billion-company-and-200-million-fortune-selling-parents-peace-of-mind/|accessdate = 2015-06-15|first = Clare|last = O'Connor}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Jessica Alba Opens Up On Being A Successful Businesswoman|url = http://www.latintimes.com/jessica-alba-being-successful-businesswoman-people-pretty-much-expected-nothing-me-318367|accessdate = 2015-06-15|date = 22 May 2015|last = Roiz|first = Jessica Lucia|publisher = Latin Times}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = 10 Most Powerful Women Entrepreneurs|url = http://fortune.com/2012/09/27/10-most-powerful-women-entrepreneurs/|accessdate = 2015-06-15|date = 27 September 2012|publisher = Fortune|first = Colleen|last = Leahey}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.maxim.com/maxim-man/iconoclasts/article/we-weren%E2%80%99t-joking-jessica-alba-serious-businesswoman|title = We Weren't Joking, Jessica Alba Is a Serious Businesswoman|date = 28 August 2014|accessdate = 2015-06-15|website = |publisher = Maxim|last = Burmon|first = Andrew}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Jessica Alba Does It All: Mom, Actress, Businesswoman|url = http://www.inquisitr.com/1210089/jessica-alba-does-it-all-mom-actress-businesswoman/|accessdate = 2015-06-15|date = 12 April 2014|publisher = Inquisitr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Jessica Alba Covers Forbes' Richest Self Made Woman!|url = http://www.msn.com/en-ae/health/medical/jessica-alba-covers-forbes-richest-self-made-woman/vp-BBkoKah|website = www.msn.com|accessdate = 2015-06-15|publisher = Perform UK|date = 30 May 2015}}</ref>  She has won various awards for her acting, including the Choice Actress [[Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Award]] and [[Saturn Award for Best Actress on Television]], and a [[Golden Globe Award|Golden Globe]] nomination for her lead role in the television series ''[[Dark Angel (TV series)|Dark Angel]]''.<ref name=\"golden angel\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2000/12/28/jessica-alba-golden-globe-nominee-best-actress|title=Jessica Alba is a Golden Globe nominee for Best Actress?|first=Ken|last=Tucker|date=December 28, 2000|publisher=EW.com|accessdate=May 23, 2015}}</ref>\n\nAlba began her television and movie appearances at age 13 in ''[[Camp Nowhere]]'' and ''[[The Secret World of Alex Mack]]'' (1994). She rose to prominence as the lead actress in the [[James Cameron]] [[Television program#Seasons/series|television series]] ''[[Dark Angel (TV series)|Dark Angel]]'' (2000\u20132002) when she was 19 years old.<ref name=\"cbs\"/><ref name=\"peoplebio\"/> Alba later appeared in ''[[Honey (2003 film)|Honey]]'' (2003), ''[[Sin City (film)|Sin City]]'' (2005), ''[[Fantastic Four (2005 film)|Fantastic Four]]'' (2005), ''[[Into the Blue (2005 film)|Into the Blue]]'' (2005), ''[[Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer]]'' (2007) and ''[[Good Luck Chuck]]'' (2007).<ref name=\"theage\"/>\n\nIn January 2012, Alba co-founded [[The Honest Company]], a consumer goods company that sells non-toxic household products, and owns 15 to 20 percent of the company.<ref name=\"People\">{{cite web|url=http://celebritybabies.people.com/2012/01/19/jessica-alba-launches-the-honest-company/ |title=Jessica Alba Launches The Honest Company|date=January 19, 2012 |accessdate=March 20, 2012 |work=[[People (magazine)|People]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=O'Connor|first1=Clare|title=How Jessica Alba Built A $1 Billion Company, And $200 Million Fortune, Selling Parents Peace Of Mind|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/clareoconnor/2015/05/27/how-jessica-alba-built-a-1-billion-company-and-200-million-fortune-selling-parents-peace-of-mind/|website=forbes.com|publisher=Forbes|accessdate=3 August 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nAlba was born in [[Pomona, California]],<ref name=filmref /> to Catherine Louisa (n\u00e9e Jensen) and Mark David Alba. Her mother has [[Danish people|Danish]], [[Welsh people|Welsh]], [[Germans|German]], [[English people|English]], and [[French people|French]] ancestry, while her paternal grandparents, who were born in California, were both the children of [[Mexican people|Mexican]] immigrants.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Hollywood Now: New Fall Previews - InterfaithFamily|url = http://www.interfaithfamily.com/arts_and_entertainment/popular_culture/Hollywood_Now_New_Fall_Previews.shtml|website = www.interfaithfamily.com|accessdate = 2015-06-15|date = 29 August 2014|last = Miller|first = Gerri}}</ref><ref>[https://books.google.ca/books?id=2sg3CwAAQBAJ&pg=PA383&dq=%22Catherine+Louisa+Jensen%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjf7N7bnr3LAhUovYMKHUjTA6sQ6AEIFzAA]</ref> She has a younger brother, [[Joshua Alba|Joshua]]. Her third cousin, once removed, is writer [[Gustavo Arellano]].<ref>http://blogs.ocweekly.com/navelgazing/2010/01/gustavo_related_to_jessica_alb.php</ref> Her father's [[United States Air Force|Air Force]] career took the family to [[Biloxi, Mississippi]], and [[Del Rio, Texas]], before settling back in [[Claremont, California]], when she was nine years old.<ref name=\"peoplebio\"/><ref name=\"indalba\"/> Alba has described her family as being a \"very conservative family \u2013 a traditional, Catholic, Latin American family\" and herself as very liberal; she says she had identified herself as a \"[[Feminism|feminist]]\" as early as age five.<ref name=elle-changeling>{{cite web | work=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]] | url = http://www.elle.com/Entertainment/Cover-Shoots/The-Changeling2/Jessica-Alba2 | accessdate =June 23, 2009 | title = The Changeling | first = Maggie | last = Bullock | date = February 4, 2009}}</ref>\n\nAlba's early life was marked by a multitude of physical maladies. During childhood, she suffered from [[Atelectasis|partially collapsed lungs]] twice, had [[pneumonia]] four to five times a year, as well as a ruptured [[Vermiform appendix|appendix]] and a [[tonsil]]lar cyst.<ref name=peoplebio /> Alba became isolated from other children at school, because she was in the hospital so often due to her illnesses that no one knew her well enough to befriend her.<ref>{{cite journal |magazine=[[OK!]] |pages=34\u201339 |date=October 3, 2005 |title=OK!}}</ref> Alba has also had [[asthma]] since she was a child.<ref name=peoplebio /> Alba has said that her family's frequent moving also contributed to her isolation from her peers.<ref name=elle-changeling /> She has acknowledged that she suffered from [[obsessive\u2013compulsive disorder]] during her childhood.<ref>{{cite news| url = http://www.news.com.au/entertainment/story/0,23663,22244110-5006050,00.html| title = My obsession |last = Cullen | first = Denise | format = Reprint from Sunday Telegraph| publisher=[[News.com.au]]| date = August 19, 2007 | accessdate =December 12, 2007}}</ref><ref>Interview on ''[[The Tonight Show with Jay Leno]]''; September 26, 2005</ref> Alba graduated from [[Claremont High School (Claremont, California)|Claremont High School]] at age 16,<ref>[http://www.contactmusic.com/info/jessica_alba \"Jessica Alba \u2013 Contactmusic.com\"]. ''contactmusic.com''. Retrieved August 1, 2010.</ref> and she subsequently attended the [[Atlantic Theater Company]].<ref name=\"peoplealba\">{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/jessica_alba |title=Jessica Alba|accessdate=April 23, 2008 |work=[[People (magazine)|People]]}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\n\n===Beginnings (1992\u20131999)===\n[[File:Jessica Alba Cropped2.png|thumb|upright|right|Alba in 2007]]\n\nAlba expressed interest in acting from the age of five. In 1992, the 11-year-old Alba persuaded her mother to take her to an acting competition in [[Beverly Hills, California|Beverly Hills]], whose grand prize was free acting classes. Alba won the grand prize, and took her first acting lessons. An agent signed Alba nine months later.<ref name=\"peoplebio\"/><ref name=peoplealba /> Her first appearance on film was a small role in the 1994 feature ''[[Camp Nowhere]]'' as Gail. She was originally hired for two weeks but her role turned into a two-month job when one of the prominent actresses dropped out.<ref name=\"cbs\"/>\n\nAlba appeared in two national television commercials for [[Nintendo]] and [[J. C. Penney]] as a child. She was later featured in several [[independent film]]s. She branched out into television in 1994 with a recurring role as the vain Jessica in three episodes of the [[Nickelodeon]] comedy series ''[[The Secret World of Alex Mack]]''.<ref name=\"peoplebio\">{{cite web|url = http://www.people.com/people/jessica_alba/biography|title = Jessica Alba: Biography|accessdate = April 24, 2008|work = [[People (magazine)|People]]|publisher = Time Inc}}</ref> She then performed the role of Maya in the first two seasons of the television series ''[[Flipper (1995 TV series)|Flipper]]''.<ref name=\"cbs\"/><ref name=\"peoplebio\"/> Under the tutelage of her [[lifeguard]] mother, Alba learned to swim before she could walk, and she was a [[Professional Association of Diving Instructors|PADI]]-certified [[scuba diving|scuba diver]], skills which were put to use on the show, which was filmed in Australia.<ref name=\"peoplebio\"/><ref name=\"daily\">{{cite web|url=http://iworks.factiva.com/du/iworksarticledisplay.aspx?napc=v&acc=DAISTA0020051018e1ag0008j|title=Water babe Jess in big screen splash |format=paid registration required |accessdate=April 24, 2008 |work=Daily Star |location=UK |date=October 16, 2005}}</ref>\n\nIn 1998, she appeared as Melissa Hauer in a first-season episode of the [[Steven Bochco]] crime-drama ''[[Brooklyn South]]'', as Leanne in two episodes of ''[[Beverly Hills, 90210]]'', and as Layla in an episode of ''[[The Love Boat: The Next Wave]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Love Boat: The Next Wave Episodes on UPN|url=http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/love-boat-the-next-wave-1998/episode-2-season-1/remember/202782|publisher=[[TV Guide]]|accessdate=August 7, 2013}}</ref> In 1999, she appeared in the [[Randy Quaid]] comedy feature ''[[P.U.N.K.S.]]''.<ref name=\"cbs\">{{cite web |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2005/03/28/earlyshow/leisure/celebspot/main683508.shtml |title=Jessica Alba Goes To 'Sin City' |accessdate=April 24, 2008 |work=[[CBS]] |date=March 28, 2005}}</ref> After Alba graduated from high school, she studied acting with [[William H. Macy]] and his wife, [[Felicity Huffman]], at the [[Atlantic Theater Company]], which was developed by Macy and [[Pulitzer Prize]]-winning playwright and film director, [[David Mamet]].<ref name=\"peoplealba\"/><ref>{{Cite web|title = FEATURED ALUMNI|url = https://atlanticactingschool.org/alumni/|website = atlanticactingschool.org|accessdate = 2015-06-15}}</ref>\nAlba rose to greater prominence in [[Hollywood, Los Angeles, California|Hollywood]] in 1999 after appearing as a member of a snobby high school clique in the [[Drew Barrymore]] romantic comedy ''[[Never Been Kissed]]'', and as the female lead in the 1999 comedy-horror film ''[[Idle Hands]]'', opposite [[Devon Sawa]].<ref name=\"theage\"/>\n\n===Breakout (2000\u20132008)===\n[[File:Jessica-Alba-The-Eye.JPG|alt=Smiling young woman in strapless white dress, holding a microphone.|thumb|upright|left|Alba at the 2008 Paris premiere for ''[[The Eye (2008 film)|The Eye]]'']]\n\nHer big break came when writer/director [[James Cameron]] picked Alba from a pool of 1,200 candidates for the role of the genetically engineered super-soldier, [[Max Guevara]], on the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] sci-fi television series ''[[Dark Angel (TV series)|Dark Angel]]''. Co-created by Cameron, the series starred Alba, and ran for two seasons until 2002, earning her critical acclaim as well as a [[Golden Globe Award|Golden Globe nomination]].<ref name=\"theage\">{{cite web |url=http://www.theage.com.au/news/film/look-at-me/2007/06/21/1182019240554.html |title=Look at me |accessdate=April 24, 2008 |work=The Age |location=Australia |date=June 22, 2007}}</ref><ref name=\"seattletimes\">{{cite web |last=Lawson |first=Terry |url=http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/entertainment/2001805635_jessicaalba03.html |title=Look at me |accessdate=April 24, 2008 |work=[[The Seattle Times]] |date=December 8, 2003}}</ref> Alba later admitted to suffering from [[anorexia nervosa|anorexia]] while in preparation for ''Dark Angel''.<ref name=\"askmenalba\">{{cite web |url = http://uk.askmen.com/celebs/entertainment-news/jessica-alba/jessica-alba-anorexic-hell.html|title = Jessica Alba's anorexic hell|accessdate = April 23, 2008|work = [[AskMen.com]]|date = July 27, 2005}}</ref>\n\nAlba has been well received in popular culture. She received the [[Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Award]] for \"Choice Actress\" and [[Saturn Award for Best Actress on Television|Saturn Award for Best Actress]] for her role in ''Dark Angel''. In 2006, Alba received an [[MTV Movie Awards 2006|MTV Movie Award]] for \"Sexiest Performance\" for ''[[Sin City (film)|Sin City]]''.<ref name=\"maxim\"/><ref name=\"askmenprofile\">{{cite web |url = http://uk.askmen.com/celebs/women/actress_60/61_jessica_alba.html|title = Jessica Alba|accessdate = April 24, 2008|work = [[AskMen.com]]}}</ref> Her acting has also drawn criticism, however, as she was nominated for the [[Golden Raspberry Awards|Razzie]] Award for Worst Actress in 2005 for her performances in ''[[Fantastic Four (2005 film)|Fantastic Four]]'' and ''[[Into the Blue (2005 film)|Into the Blue]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.razzies.com/history/05nomActr.asp|title = Razzies 2005 Nominees for Worst Actress|work = [[Razzie Awards]]|accessdate = September 2, 2009|last = Wilson|first = John|date = 2005|publisher = GOLDEN RASPBERRY AWARD FOUNDATION}}</ref> She was nominated for the same award for 2007's ''[[Awake (film)|Awake]]'', ''[[Good Luck Chuck]]'', and ''[[Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.razzies.com/history/07nomActr.asp|title = 28th Annual Razzie Award Nominees for Worst Actress|work = [[Razzie Awards]]|date = 2007|accessdate = 2015-06-15|publisher = GOLDEN RASPBERRY AWARD FOUNDATION|last = Wilson|first = John}}</ref>\n\nAlba's film roles have included an aspiring dancer-choreographer in ''[[Honey (2003 film)|Honey]]'', [[exotic dancer]] [[Nancy Callahan]] in ''[[Sin City (film)|Sin City]]'', and as the [[Marvel Comics]] character Sue Storm, the [[Invisible Woman]], in ''Fantastic Four'' and [[Fantastic Four: Rise of the Silver Surfer|its sequel]]. She also starred in ''Into the Blue'' (2005) and ''[[Good Luck Chuck]]'' (2007).<ref name=\"sfchronicle\">{{cite news |url=http://www.sfgate.com/cgi-bin/article.cgi?f=/c/a/2005/07/08/DDGQ2DJSU21.DTL&type=movies |title=Fantastic Four Movie Review |accessdate=May 16, 2008 |work=The San Francisco Chronicle |date=July 8, 2005 | first=Mick | last=LaSalle}}</ref><ref name=\"usatoday\">{{cite news |url=http://www.usatoday.com/life/movies/news/2003-11-30-alba-honey_x.htm |title=Jessica Alba flows like 'Honey' |accessdate=April 24, 2008 |work=USA Today |date=November 30, 2003 | first=James | last=Endrst}}</ref> Alba hosted the [[2006 MTV Movie Awards]] and performed sketches spoofing the movies ''[[King Kong (2005 film)|King Kong]]'', ''[[Mission: Impossible 3]]'', and ''[[The Da Vinci Code (film)|The Da Vinci Code]]''.<ref name=\"mtvmovie\">{{cite web |url = http://www.mtv.com/ontv/movieawards/archive/year.jhtml?year=2006#summary|title = 2006 MTV Movie Awards|accessdate = April 24, 2008|publisher = MTV|date = 8 June 2006}}</ref> In February 2008, she hosted the [[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]]' [[Academy Award, Scientific or Technical|Science and Technical Awards]].<ref name=\"apkesq\">{{cite news |url=http://www.kesq.com/Global/story.asp?S=7850086&nav=menu191_2_1 |title=Jessica Alba dazzles self-professed nerds as academy hands out science and tech Oscars |accessdate=April 23, 2008 |agency=[[Associated Press]] |publisher=Kesq.com |date=February 10, 2008 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20080605230922/http://www.kesq.com/Global/story.asp?S=7850086&nav=menu191_2_1 |archivedate = June 5, 2008}}</ref> Alba has been represented by talent agents [[Patrick Whitesell]]<ref>{{cite news |first=Claude |last=Brodesser |url=http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117794355.html?categoryid=18&cs=1 |title=Whitesell exits CAA |work=Variety |date=February 27, 2001 |accessdate=September 2, 2009}}</ref> and Brad Cafarelli.<ref name=\"playboy\"/>\n\nIn 2008, Alba made her acting transition to the horror-film genre in ''[[The Eye (2007 film)|The Eye]]'', a remake of the Hong Kong original.<ref name=\"indalba\"/> The film was released on February 1, 2008. Though the film was not well received by critics,<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/10008606-eye/|title = The Eye|accessdate = February 2, 2008|work = [[Rotten Tomatoes]]|date = 2008|publisher = Rotten Tomatoes}}</ref> Alba's performance itself received mixed reviews.  Alba won a [[Teen Choice Award|Teen Choice for Choice Movie Actress: Horror/Thriller]] and a [[Razzie Award for Worst Actress]]-nomination.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Jessica Alba|url = http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0004695/awards|website = IMDb|accessdate = 2015-06-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Razzies\u00ae 2008 Nominees for Worst Actress|url = http://www.razzies.com/history/08nomActr.asp|website = www.razzies.com|accessdate = 2015-06-15|date = 2008|publisher = GOLDEN RASPBERRY AWARD FOUNDATION|last = Wilson|first = John}}</ref> Also in 2008, Alba starred alongside [[Mike Myers (actor)|Mike Myers]] and [[Justin Timberlake]] in \"box office bomb\" ''[[The Love Guru]]''. Alba was nominated for a [[Razzie Award for Worst Actress]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Razzies\u00ae 2008 Nominees for Worst Actress|url = http://www.razzies.com/history/08nomActr.asp|website = www.razzies.com|accessdate = 2015-06-15|date = 2008|last = Wilson|first = John|publisher = THE GOLDEN RASPBERRY AWARD FOUNDATION}}</ref>\n\nIn late 2008, Alba signed on to star as the lead role in ''[[An Invisible Sign of My Own (film)|An Invisible Sign of My Own]]''.<ref name=invisible>{{cite news | last = Heath | first = Paul | url = http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117991811.html?categoryid=13&cs=1 | title = Jessica Alba Turns 'Invisible' |work=Variety | date = September 8, 2008 | accessdate =September 21, 2010}}</ref> The movie finished filming in November 2008.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.screeninglog.com/journal/2008/11/5/jessica-alba-spotted-on-invisible-sign-set.html |title=Jessica Alba spotted on Invisible Set |last=Tabouring |first=Franck |work=Screening Blog |date=November 5, 2008 |accessdate=June 26, 2009}}</ref> It premiered at the [[Hamptons International Film Festival]] and was released to theaters in May 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=HIFF 2010 Program Announced|url=http://hamptonsfilmfest.org/2010/09/2010hiffprogra/|publisher=hamptonsfilmfest.org|accessdate=May 28, 2012|date=September 15, 2010}}</ref><ref>[http://www.ifcfilms.com/films/an-invisible-sign \"An Invisible Sign\"]. ''IFC Entertainment''. Retrieved March 17, 2011.</ref>\n\n=== 2010\u2013present===\n[[File:Jessica Alba 2010.jpg|thumb|upright|right|Alba in 2010.]]\nIn 2010, Alba starred in five films. She played Joyce Lakeland, a prostitute in ''[[The Killer Inside Me (2010 film)|The Killer Inside Me]]'', film adaption of the book of the same name which co-starred [[Kate Hudson]] and [[Casey Affleck]]. The film premiered at the [[Sundance Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bloody-disgusting.com/news/14372 |title='Killer Inside Me' Finds New Director and Cast |work=[[Bloody Disgusting]] |date=November 17, 2008 |accessdate=June 26, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/news/e3i5c6f976cbed5f4a94581e2325dd5cb87 |last=Borys |first=Kit |title=Simon Baker nabs 'Killer' role |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=May 11, 2009 |accessdate=May 18, 2009 |subscription=yes |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20090515102118/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/news/e3i5c6f976cbed5f4a94581e2325dd5cb87 <!--Added by H3llBot--> |archivedate=May 15, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.themovieinsider.com/m4128/the-killer-inside-me/|title = The Killer Inside Me|work = The Movie Insider|accessdate = June 26, 2009|publisher = The Movie Insider LLC}}</ref> Her second film of the year was the hit romantic comedy ''[[Valentine's Day (2010 film)|Valentine's Day]]'', directed by [[Garry Marshall]].<ref name=hollywoodreporter>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/hr/content_display/news/e3i5c6f976cbed5f4a9fe5dace4b5f95d99 |title=The Hollywood Reporter |date=May 11, 2009 |accessdate=September 2, 2009 |subscription=yes |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/20090516180725/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com:80/hr/content_display/news/e3i5c6f976cbed5f4a9fe5dace4b5f95d99? |archivedate=May 16, 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.buzzsugar.com/Garry-Marshall-Gets-Cast-Valentines-Day-3143951|title = Garry Marshall Gets a Cast For ''Valentine's Day''|work = Buzzsugar|accessdate = September 21, 2010|date = 5 December 2009}}</ref> She portrayed [[Ashton Kutcher]]'s girlfriend, Morley Clarkson, in the ensemble film that included [[Julia Roberts]], [[Anne Hathaway]], [[Jessica Biel]], [[Bradley Cooper]], and [[Jennifer Garner]], among others.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.empireonline.com/news/feed.asp?NID=25155 |title=Three More Join Valentine's Day |last=Hewitt |first=Chris |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=June 26, 2009}}</ref> It was released on February 12, 2010.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0817230/|title = Valentine's Day|date = |accessdate = 2015-06-15|website = IMDb|publisher = |last = |first = }}</ref> Later in the year, she appeared in action film ''[[Machete (film)|Machete]]'', in ''An Invisible Sign of My Own'' and in ''[[Little Fockers]]'', reuniting with [[Robert De Niro]] who was also in ''Machete''.\nIn August 2010, it was announced that Alba would appear in ''[[Spy Kids: All the Time in the World|Spy Kids 4]]''.<ref>[http://movies.sky.com/jessica-alba-heading-spy-kids-reboot Jessica Alba to Star in Spy Kids 4]</ref> The film was released a year later.\n\nIn January 2012, Alba and business partner Chris Gavigan launched [[The Honest Company]], a collection of toxin-free household goods, diapers, and body care products.<ref name=\"People\"/> The company is currently valued at $1 billion.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lorenzetti|first1=Laura|title=Jessica Alba startup The Honest Co. raises $70 million as it heads toward IPO|url=http://fortune.com/2014/08/26/jessica-alba-honest-co-ipo/|accessdate=10 March 2015|work=[[Fortune (magazine)]]|date=26 August 2014}}</ref> In March 2012, Alba announced that she will be releasing a book, ''The Honest Life,'' based on her experiences creating a natural, non-toxic life for her family. The book, slated for release in early 2013, will be published by [[Rodale Inc.|Rodale]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20579896,00.html |title=Jessica Alba to Release Her First Book|date=March 19, 2012|accessdate=March 20, 2012 |work=[[People (magazine)|People]]}}</ref>\n\nHer 2013 projects include comedy ''[[A.C.O.D.]]''<ref>{{cite web|title=Adam Scott Joins A.C.O.D.|url=http://www.movieweb.com/news/adam-scott-joins-a-c-o-d|publisher=MovieWeb.com|accessdate=May 28, 2012|date=August 17, 2011}}</ref> and animated film ''[[Escape from Planet Earth]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sarah Jessica Parker, Jessica Alba Join 'Escape from Planet Earth'|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/sarah-jessica-parker-jessica-alba-218117|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=May 28, 2012|date=August 2, 2011}}</ref> Alba reprised her roles, Santana in ''Machete'''s sequel ''[[Machete Kills]]'',<ref>{{cite web|title='Machete Kills' Casting News|url=http://www.planetfury.com/content/machete-kills-casting|publisher=Planet Fury|accessdate=May 28, 2012|date=May 7, 2012}}</ref> and Nancy Callahan in ''[[Sin City: A Dame to Kill For]]'', the sequel to 2005's ''Sin City''.<ref name=sincity2>{{cite web|last=Lyttelton|first=Oliver|title='Sin City: A Dame To Kill For' Hits Theaters On October 4th, 2013, Jessica Alba & Mickey Rourke Confirmed|url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/sin-city-a-dame-to-kill-for-hits-theaters-on-october-4th-2013-jessica-alba-mickey-rourke-confirmed-20120517|work=The Playlist|publisher=[[IndieWire]]|accessdate=May 28, 2012|date=May 17, 2012}}</ref> Filming for the ''Sin City'' sequel started in October 2012 and the film was released in August 2014.<ref name=sincity2/>\n\n== Public image ==\n\nIn 2001, Alba was ranked No. 1 on ''[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]]'' magazine's Hot 100 list. She said that \"I have to go to certain lengths to use sexuality to my advantage, while guiding people to thinking the way I want them to.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/jessica_alba/biography/0,,20005720_10,00.html |title=Jessica Alba Biography |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |accessdate=June 25, 2009|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20080310031506/http://www.people.com/people/jessica_alba/biography/0,,20005720_0,00.html | archivedate=March 10, 2008}}</ref> In 2005, Alba was named one of ''[[People (magazine)|People]]'' magazine's 50 Most Beautiful People, and also appeared in the magazine's 100 Most Beautiful list in 2007. In 2002, Alba was voted as the fifth Sexiest Female Star for 2002 in a Hollywood.com poll, No.4 in the Top 10 Sci-Fi Babes, No.6 in ''FHM'''s Sexiest Girls for their poll, and ranked at No.12 in ''Stuff'' magazine's \"102 Sexiest Women in the World\" 2002 edition.{{citation needed|date=April 2015}} In 2005, Alba was ranked at No.5 on the ''Maxim'' magazine's Hot 100 list.{{citation needed|date=April 2015}}\n\nOn the cover of the March 2006 issue, ''[[Playboy]]'' magazine named Alba among its 25 Sexiest Celebrities, and the Sex Star of the Year. Alba was involved in litigation against ''Playboy'' for its use of her image (from a promotional shot for ''Into the Blue'') without her consent, which she contends gave the appearance that she was featured in the issue in a \"nude pictorial\". However, she later dropped the lawsuit after receiving a personal apology from ''Playboy'' owner [[Hugh Hefner]], who agreed to make donations to two charities that Alba has supported.<ref name=\"playboy\">{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,1180254,00.html |title=Playboy Apologizes to Jessica Alba |last=Silverman |first=Stephen M. |accessdate=September 21, 2010 |work=[[People (magazine)|People]]}}</ref>\n\nWhen reports surfaced that a 21-year-old Chinese girl was seeking plastic surgery to resemble Alba in order to win back an ex-boyfriend, the star spoke out against the perceived need to change one's appearance for love.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nationalledger.com/ledgerpop/article_272630303.shtml|title=Jessica Alba Makeover (Photos) \u2013 Plastic Surgery to Look Like Actress|work=National Ledger|date=February 7, 2010|accessdate=Feb 10, 2010}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Jessica Alba at Fantastic Four- Rise London Premiere 5.jpg|alt=Smiling young woman with wavy hair pulled up in a loose bun, wearing a gold low-cut dress and accompanied by a man. She is signing autographs.|thumb|upright|Alba in 2007 at the London premiere of ''Fantastic Four'']]\n\n{{quote box|width=35%|align=left|quote=\"I think there are ambitious girls who will do anything to be famous, and they think men in this business are used to women doing that. Contrary to how people may feel, I've never used my sexuality. That's not part of it for me. When I'm in a meeting, I want to tell you why I'm an asset, how I'm a commodity, how I can put asses in the seats, not, 'There's a chance you're going to be able to fuck me.' That's never been my deal.\"|source=Alba on not using her sex appeal in order to get her goals in her acting career, 2008<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.elle.com/Entertainment/Cover-Shoots/Don-t-Mess-With-Jess |title=Don't Mess With Jess |accessdate=25 June 2009 |work=[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]}}</ref>}}\n\nIn 2006, Alba ranked No.3 on E! Television's 101 Sexiest Celebrity Bodies. In 2006 readers of [[AskMen.com]] voted Alba No. 1 on ''99 Most Desirable Women'',<ref name=\"askmenalba2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.askmen.com/specials/2006_top_99/jessica-alba-1.html|title=Jessica Alba (profile)|accessdate=April 23, 2008|work=[[AskMen.com]]|year=2006}}</ref> while in 2007, ''Maxim Magazine'' placed Alba on the number 2 spot of their \"Top 100\".<ref name=\"maxim\">{{cite web|url=http://www.maximonline.com/Girls/Jessicaalba/slideshow/1126/47.aspx?src=GM7070:MD |title=Maxim Top 100 for 2007 |accessdate=April 23, 2008 |work=[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]] |year=2007 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/20080605083030/http://www.maximonline.com:80/Girls/Jessicaalba/slideshow/1126/47.aspx?src=GM7070:MD |archivedate=June 5, 2008 }}</ref> Both ''[[GQ]]'' and ''[[InStyle|In Style]]'' had Alba on their June 2008 covers,<ref name=\"menstyle\">{{cite web|url=http://video.men.style.com/?fr_story=6d59b836ad0746f01d5e61f3986e4825313460a5&rf=bm|title=GQ: The Jessica Alba Video|accessdate=April 23, 2008|work=[[Style.com]]}}</ref><ref name=\"instyle\">{{cite web|url=http://www.instyle.com/instyle/products/productfinder/issue/0,,1625011,00.html|title=In Style June 2007|accessdate=April 23, 2008|work=[[InStyle]]|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20080222193705/http://www.instyle.com/instyle/products/productfinder/issue/0,,1625011,00.html <!--Added by H3llBot-->|archivedate=February 22, 2008}}</ref> and in May, after eight million votes, ''FHM'' (UK and USA editions) named Alba the winner as \"2007's Sexiest Woman in the World\".<ref>[http://www.fhm.com/girls/covergirls/jessica-alba Jessica Alba at FHM.com]</ref> Alba has been regarded as one of the world's most attractive women, being named to Maxim's Hot 100 in 2008.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.maxim.com/Girls/34JessicaAlba/slideshow/24847/2463.aspx |title=2009 Hot 100 |work=[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]] |accessdate=June 25, 2009 |date=May 6, 2009 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20090616172036/http://maxim.com/Girls/34JessicaAlba/slideshow/24847/2463.aspx <!--Added by H3llBot--> |archivedate=June 16, 2009}}</ref> In 2007, Alba was ranked in at No.1 in FHM's Sexiest Girls of 2007 poll, in the magazine's [[Latvia]]n edition. Alba was ranked No.4 on Empire Magazine's 100 Sexiest Movie Stars in 2007. In 2006 and 2007, Alba was voted No.1 as the most sexy woman in the world by the Norwegian FHM.{{citation needed|date=April 2015}} Alba appeared in the 2009 [[Campari]] calendar. Campari printed 9,999 copies of the calendar featuring photos of Alba posing sexually in swimsuits, and high heels.<ref name=\"Jessica Alba Bares Body After Baby for Calendar\">{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20243751,00.html |title=Jessica Alba Bares Body After Baby For Calendar |accessdate=June 25, 2009 |work=[[People (magazine)|People]]}}</ref> In 2008, Alba was ranked No.34 on ''Maxim'' magazine's Hot 100 list, was ranked No.2 on ''Wizard'' magazine's \"Sexiest Women of TV\" list, and was named in ''GQ'' Magazine one of the 25 Sexiest Women in film of all time.{{citation needed|date=April 2015}} Alba is the only woman who has made the ''Maxim Magazine'' Hot 100 list in all the years it was published; from 2000 to 2014.<ref name=\"Maxim Hot 100 Stats\">{{cite web |url=http://www.loodzwaar.com/2014/06/16/maxim-hot-100-van-2014/#maxim-hot-100-summary |title=Maxim Hot 100 Stats |accessdate=June 16, 2014 |work=Loodzwaar.com}}</ref> She appeared on Maxim's 2014 Hot 100 list, finishing 8.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Maxim 2014 Hot 100 |url=http://www.maxim.com/hot100/2014 |journal=Maxim |accessdate=June 16, 2014}}</ref> She was named one of the \"100 Hottest Women of All-Time\" by ''[[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=The 100 Hottest Women of All-Time|url=http://www.menshealth.com/sex-women/hottest-women-all-time|work=[[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]]|accessdate=January 3, 2012|year=2011}}</ref> ''People'' named her one of 2012 Most Beautiful at Every Age.<ref>{{cite web|title=2012 Most Beautiful at Every Age \u2013 Jessica Alba|url=http://www.people.com/people/package/gallery/0,,20360857_20360861,00.html#20612529|work=People|accessdate=April 25, 2012|author=Karen J. Quan|date=April 20, 2012}}</ref>\n\nAlba fears being typecast as a [[sex kitten]] based on the bulk of parts offered to her, commenting, \"Somehow, I don't think this is happening to [[Natalie Portman]].\"<ref name=\"afwt\"/> In the interview, Alba said she wants to be taken seriously as an actress but believes she needs to do movies that she would otherwise not be interested in to build her career, stating that eventually she hopes to be more selective in her film projects.<ref name=\"afwt\">{{cite web |url=http://www.moono.com/news/news01099.html |title=Alba Fears Whore Typecast |accessdate=July 31, 2007 |work=WEEN |publisher=Moono |date=November 9, 2005}}</ref> Alba also maintains a strict [[nudity clause|no-nudity clause]] in her contract. She was given the option to appear nude in ''Sin City'' by the film's directors, [[Frank Miller (comics)|Frank Miller]] and [[Robert Rodriguez]], but declined the offer, saying, \"I don't do nudity. I just don't. Maybe that makes me a bad actress. Maybe I won't get hired in some things. But I have too much anxiety\".<ref name=Elle2006/> She remarked of a ''[[GQ]]'' shoot in which she was scantily clad, \"They didn't want me to wear the granny panties, but I said, 'If I'm gonna be topless I need to wear granny panties.\"<ref name=\"christian\">{{cite web |last=Gardetta |first=Dave |url=http://www.contactmusic.com/new/xmlfeed.nsf/mndwebpages/alba%20turns%20her%20back%20on%20christian%20pals%20who%20made%20her%20feel%20ashamed |title=Alba Turns Her Back on Christian Pals Who Made Her Feel Ashamed |accessdate=April 23, 2008 |work=[[GQ]] |publisher=[[Contactmusic.com]] |date=March 23, 2005}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\n\nAlba was raised as a Catholic<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movies.msn.com/movies/article.aspx?news=458443&gt1=28101|title=Jessica Alba says she'll never do a nude scene |publisher=Movies.msn.com|date=February 14, 2010|accessdate=September 2, 2012}}</ref> throughout her teenage years,<ref>{{cite web |last=Gardetta|first=Dave|url=http://men.style.com/gq/features/full?id=content_847 |title=The Sinner|accessdate=April 23, 2008 |work=[[GQ]]|publisher=[[Style.com]]|date=April 2005 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20080416165610/http://men.style.com/gq/features/full?id=content_847 |archivedate = April 16, 2008}}</ref> but left the church after four years because she felt she was being judged for her appearance, explaining: <blockquote>\"Older men would hit on me, and my youth pastor said it was because I was wearing provocative clothing, when I wasn't. It just made me feel like if I was in any way desirable to the opposite sex that it was my fault, and it made me ashamed of my body and being a woman\".<ref>{{cite web | date=October 11, 2006 | accessdate=May 14, 2009 | title=Alba Alters Religious Beliefs | url=http://www.moono.com/news/news03203.html | publisher=moono.com}}</ref></blockquote>\n\nAlba also had objections to the church's condemnations of premarital sex and homosexuality, and what she saw as a lack of strong [[Women in the Bible|female role models in the Bible]], explaining \"I thought it was a nice guide, but it certainly wasn't how I was going to live my life.\"<ref name=\"Elle2006\">{{cite web| url = http://www.elle.com/coverstory/9917/jessica-alba.html| title = Jessica Alba \u2013 ELLE | last = Itzkoff | first = Dave | publisher=Elle.com| accessdate =December 12, 2007}}</ref> Her \"religious devotion [began] to wane\" at the age of 15 when she guest-starred as a teenager with [[gonorrhea]] in the throat in a 1996 episode of the television series ''[[Chicago Hope]]''. Her friends at church reacted negatively to her role, making her lose faith in the church.<ref name=autogenerated2>{{cite web|author=Jessica Alba |url=http://www.people.com/people/jessica_alba/biography |title=Jessica Alba Biography |work=People |accessdate=September 2, 2009}}</ref> However, she has stated that she still holds her belief in God despite leaving the church.<ref name=\"new\">{{cite web |url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_m0EIN/is_2001_Sept_10/ai_78019584|title=Glamour's October Cover Girl \u2013 Dark Angel Jessica Alba Reveals Her Obsessions, Love, and God \u2013 p.256; October issue on newsstands Sept. 11, 2001 | work=Glamour Magazine|accessdate=May 18, 2008 |year=2008 }}</ref>\n\nWhile filming ''Dark Angel'' in January 2000, Alba began a three-year relationship with her co-star [[Michael Weatherly]], which caused controversy due to their 12-year age difference.{{citation needed|date=April 2015}} Weatherly proposed to Alba on her twentieth birthday, which she accepted.<ref name=\"indalba\">{{cite news |url=http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/film-and-tv/features/jessica-alba-she-wooed-hollywood-with-her-sultry-looks-ndash-but-now-shes-getting-serious-812464.html |title=Jessica Alba: She wooed Hollywood with her sultry looks \u2013 but now she's getting serious |last=Mottram|first=James|accessdate=April 23, 2008 |work=The Independent  |location=UK | date=April 21, 2008 |archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20080421225750/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/film-and-tv/features/jessica-alba-she-wooed-hollywood-with-her-sultry-looks-ndash-but-now-shes-getting-serious-812464.html <!--Added by H3llBot--> |archivedate=April 21, 2008}}</ref> In August 2003, Alba and Weatherly announced that they had ended their relationship.<ref name=peoplebio /> In July 2007, Alba spoke out about the breakup, saying \"I don't know [why I got engaged]. I was a virgin. He was 12 years older than me. I thought he knew better. My parents weren't happy. They're really religious. They believe God wouldn't allow the Bible to be written if it wasn't what they are supposed to believe. I'm completely different.\"<ref name=\"starpulse\">{{cite web|url=http://www.starpulse.com/news/index.php/2007/07/11/jessica_alba_s_parental_relationship_was/ |title=Jessica Alba's Parental Relationship Was Strained By Engagement|accessdate=April 23, 2008 |work=Starpulse|date=July 11, 2007}}</ref> Alba had at one time said she envisioned a much older man as her ideal partner, making references to [[Morgan Freeman]], [[Sean Connery]], [[Robert Redford]], and [[Michael Caine]]. She said, \"I have this thing for older men. They've been around and know so much.\"<ref name=\"femalefirst\">{{cite web|url=http://www.femalefirst.co.uk/celebrity/56902004.htm|title=Jessica Alba: Older men are ideal partners|accessdate=April 23, 2008 |work=Femalefirst.co.uk}}</ref>\n\nAlba met Cash Warren, son of actor [[Michael Warren (actor)|Michael Warren]], while filming ''Fantastic Four'' in 2004.<ref name=\"peopleengaged\">{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20168345,00.html |title=Jessica Alba Engaged!|last=Jordan|first=Julie|accessdate=April 23, 2008 |work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=December 27, 2007}}</ref><ref name=\"eonline\">{{cite web |last=Finn|first=Natalie |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/article/index.jsp?uuid=fd542a5d-6126-4059-ab62-9df839abe451&sid=fd-news |title=Jessica Alba Engaged! |accessdate=April 23, 2008 |work=[[E!]] Online |date=December 27, 2007}}</ref> Alba married Warren in Los Angeles in May 2008.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://socialitelife.celebuzz.com/2008/05/20/breaking_jessica_alba_married.php |title=Jessica Alba Marries Cash Warren |work=A Socialite's Life |date=May 20, 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20201377,00.html |title=Jessica Alba Gets Married to Cash Warren! |last=Jordan |first=Julie |work=[[People (magazine)|People Magazine]] |date=May 20, 2008}}</ref> They have two daughters: Honor Marie Warren (born 2008)<ref>{{cite news |agency=Reuters |url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/idUKSP1459620080609 |title=Jessica Alba has baby girl |date=June 9, 2008 |accessdate=September 21, 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"Jessica Alba Welcomes Baby Girl\">{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20204184,00.html |title=Jessica Alba Welcomes a Baby Girl|accessdate=June 7, 2008 |work=People |date=June 7, 2008}}</ref> and Haven Garner Warren (born 2011).<ref>[http://www.usmagazine.com/momsbabies/news/jessica-alba-gives-birth-to-daughter-haven-garner-2011148 \"Jessica Alba Gives Birth to Daughter Haven Garner!\"] August 14, 2011, US Magazine</ref> The first pictures of Honor Marie appeared in the July 2008 issue of ''[[OK!]]'' magazine, which reportedly paid $1.5&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.accesshollywood.com/top-ten-most-expensive-baby-photos_gallery_1458/image_77021 |title=Top Ten Most Expensive Baby Photos |work=Access Hollywood |accessdate=September 2, 2009}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Alba appeared in [[Henry Louis Gates]]'s genealogy series ''[[Finding Your Roots]]'', where her lineage was traced back to the modern [[Mayan civilization]].<ref>http://www.mnn.com/lifestyle/arts-culture/stories/finding-your-roots-fills-the-gaps-of-the-family-tree</ref> The show's research indicated that the surname Alba did not come from a Spanish man, since her father's direct paternal line (Y-DNA) was [[Haplogroup Q-L54]], [[Indigenous peoples of the Americas|Indigenous]] in origin. Her father's matrilineal line ([[Mtdna]]) showed [[Sephardic Jews|Sephardi Jewish]] roots, and DNA testing revealed that lawyer [[Alan Dershowitz]] is a genetic relative of hers. Jessica's global admixture was 72.7% European, 22.5% East Asian/Native American, 2% [[Sub-Saharan African]], 0.3% [[Middle Eastern]]/[[North African]], 0.1% [[South Asian]], and 2.4% \"No Match\".<ref>Stated on ''[[Finding Your Roots]]'', PBS, November 25, 2014</ref>\n\n== Charity and politics ==\n\nAlba's charity work includes participation with Clothes Off Our Back, [[Habitat for Humanity]], [[National Center for Missing and Exploited Children]], Project HOME, RADD, Revlon Run/Walk for Women, SOS Children Villages, Soles4Souls, and Step up.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/celebrity/95-jessica-alba |title=Jessica Alba's Charity Work|accessdate=April 23, 2008 |work=Celebrity Charity}}</ref> Alba endorsed and supported [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] presidential hopeful [[Barack Obama]] during the [[Barack Obama presidential primary campaign, 2008|2008 primary season]].<ref name=\"topnews\">{{cite web|url=http://www.topnews.in/light/jessica-alba,-ryan-phillippe-support-obama-new-will.i.am-video-27376 |title=Jessica Alba, Ryan Phillippe support Obama in new will.i.am video|accessdate=April 25, 2008 |work=Top News Light Reading|date=March 1, 2008}}</ref> Alba is an ambassador for the 1Goal movement to provide education to children in Africa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news/alba-gets-sporty-in-south-africa_1135987|title=Jessica Alba on Motherhood, Turning 30, and Her Sex Symbol Status|date=March 18, 2010|accessdate=April 14, 2012}}</ref> She is also a strong supporter of gay rights and on June 27, 2013, she expressed her delight with the [[Supreme Court of the United States|Supreme Court's]] decision  to strike down [[DOMA]] on her Twitter account. She tweeted \"#equality #love\".<ref>{{cite web|title=39 celebs who are super psyched about marriage equality|url=http://www.glamour.com/weddings/blogs/save-the-date/2013/06/39-more-celebs-who-are-super-p.html|publisher=Glamour|accessdate=2013-06-27}}</ref>\n\nAlba posed for a [[Bondage (BDSM)|bondage]]-themed print advertising campaign by [[Declare Yourself]], a campaign encouraging voter registration among youth for the [[United States presidential election, 2008|2008 United States presidential election]]. The ads photographed by Mark Liddell,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/marc_malkin/b28294_jessica_albas_kinky_photo_shoot.html|title=Jessica Alba's kinky photo shoot|last=Malkin|first=Marc|date=September 20, 2008|accessdate=December 28, 2008}}</ref><ref name=people2>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20224589,00.html |title=Jessica Alba's 'Shocking' Ad for Declare Yourself|date=September 10, 2008|work=People |accessdate=December 28, 2008}}</ref> which feature Alba wrapped in and gagged with black tape, drew national media attention.<ref name=people2/> Alba said of doing the advertisements that \"it didn't freak me out at all.\" Alba also said, \"I think it is important for young people to be aware of the need we have in this country to get them more active politically,\" and \"People respond to things that are shocking.\"<ref name=people2/>\n\nIn June 2009, while filming ''The Killer Inside Me'' in [[Oklahoma City]], Alba was involved in a controversy with residents when she pasted posters of sharks around town.<ref>{{cite news|title=Jessica Alba 'sorry' for shark posters|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/gossip/jessica-alba-shark-posters-article-1.376281|accessdate=October 4, 2013|newspaper=[[New York Daily News]]|date=June 9, 2009}}</ref> Alba said that she was trying to bring attention to the diminishing population of [[great white shark]]s. Media outlets speculated that Alba would be pursued and charged with vandalism.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theinsider.com/news/2266701_Oklahoma_City_police_probe_Alba_link_to_vandalism |title=Oklahoma City Police Probe Alba Link to Vandalism|work=The Insider|accessdate=June 23, 2009}}</ref> On June 16, 2009, Oklahoma City police said that they would not pursue criminal charges against Alba, because none of the property owners wanted to pursue it.<ref name=vandalism>{{cite web |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20285362,00.html |title=Jessica Alba Won't Face Vandalism Charges for Her Shark Crusade|date=June 16, 2009 | last=Meadows | first=Bob |work=People |accessdate=June 23, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theinsider.com/news/2265200_Jessica_Alba_Apologizes_for_Ill_Advised_Decision |title=Jessica Alba Apologizes for Ill Advised Decision|date=June 9, 2009|work=The Insider|accessdate=June 23, 2009}}</ref> Alba apologized in a statement to [[People (magazine)|''People'']] magazine and said that she regretted her actions.<ref name=vandalism/> She later donated an undisclosed amount of money (over $500)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.theinsider.com/news/2290507_Jessica_Alba_Donates_After_Shark_Controversy |title=Jessica Alba Donates After Controversy|date=June 18, 2009|work=The Insider|accessdate=June 23, 2009}}</ref> to the [[United Way of America|United Way]], whose billboard she had obscured with one of the shark posters.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/b130063_jessica_alba_sends_check_uniteds_way.html|title=Jessica Alba Sends Checks United Way |work=E Online |accessdate=June 23, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://blog.newsok.com/bamsblog/2009/06/20/jessica-alba-donates-to-united-way-of-central-oklahoma/ |title=Jessica Alba Donates To United Way Of Central Oklahoma |date=June 20, 2009 |work=NewsOk.com |accessdate=June 23, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5g1S3XbEGDd5qOPksNiGmQruQC0bAD98TPFAG0 |title=Alba follows apology to charity with donation |date=June 19, 2009 |agency=Associated Press |accessdate=June 23, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/2009/06/19/Alba-makes-donation-after-shark-incident/UPI-48391245440824/ |title=Alba Makes Donation After Shark Incident|date=June 19, 2009|work=Entertainment News|accessdate=June 23, 2009}}</ref>\n\nIn 2011, Alba participated in a two-day lobbying effort in Washington D.C. in support of the Safe Chemicals Act, a revision of the [[Toxic Substances Control Act of 1976]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Gavin|first=Patrick|title=Jessica Alba on the Hill|url=http://www.politico.com/click/stories/1105/jessica_alba_on_the_hill.html|newspaper=Politico|date=May 24, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Sinha|first=Vidushi|title=Pediatricians, Child Advocates Call for Passage of Safe Chemicals Act|url=http://www.voanews.com/english/news/environment/Pediatricians-Child-Advocates-Call-for-Passage-of-Safe-Chemicals-Act-122612314.html|newspaper=Voice of America|date=May 25, 2011}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Director(s)\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[Camp Nowhere]]''\n| Gail\n| [[Jonathan Prince]]\